PART 4 — Prevent Discord alert storms
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Add simple debouncing to AlertService: track the last-sent timestamp
per alert "key" (e.g. event_type + a coarse identifier), and skip
sending (just log locally instead) if an alert of the same key was
sent within the last N seconds (e.g. 60). This prevents a burst of
concurrent identical failures from all trying to hit Discord at once
and getting rate-limited — you want ONE alert telling you "fulfillment
failures happening," not fifteen attempts where most get silently
dropped by a 429.

